The paper deals with the Shannon cipher system, which is a classic topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on the security and compressibility of the cryptogram, which are key concerns in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses channel coding and rate-distortion coding, which are relevant to communication and compression (cs.CC). The paper may be of interest to researchers working on secure information transmission (cs.SI) and multimedia systems (cs.MM), as it considers the distortion associated with the reconstruction of the plaintext source.
